main event: Multiple aircraft reported sightings of unidentified lights in the sky on November 5, 1963, over Nebraska and Iowa.
interesting points: The objects changed brightness from bright to dim and back,Objects were moving at varying speeds to the southeast and northwest, Aircraft pilots reported seeing the lights for up to 25 seconds, Observers noted a stationary object as well as objects moving rapidly across the sky, The sighting involved multiple commercial and military flights in the vicinity.
witness description: Pilots from various commercial and military flights
